
            Video
            US-Somali Congresswoman-elect Ilhan Omar on hijabs in Congress
            The first Somali-American congresswoman (elect), Ilhan Omar, explains why she is campaigning for a change in the law to allow the wearing of religious head wear in Congress.A 181-year-old rule currently prohibits the wearing of hats in the House.
                
                        01 Dec 2018
                    
                
        
